column1: Before 1 January 2019, which company from among Apple, Alphabet, Amazon, and Microsoft will be the first to reach an end-of-day market capitalization of $1 trillion?
column6: ['Business', 'Finance']
column11: Leading tech companies have seen rapid increases in market capitalization (Financial Times, Reuters). Outcome will be determined by the end-of-day "Market Cap" reported by Bloomberg for Apple (AAPL), Amazon (AMZN), Alphabet (GOOGL), and Microsoft (MSFT). If two or more companies reach an end-of-day market capitalization of $1 trillion on the same day, the question will resolve on the company with the higher market capitalization.

Based on reaction in aftermarket post Apples 10-Q quarterly report published on Jul 31st. 190.29 (price close)*1.035(share price change in after market)*4,926,609(fully diluted share count in mln as per 10-Q)=970bln market cap.

After-hours price jump for Apple is making me revert back. As I discussed here [1] the relevant base rate for Apple's stock price is 68-72%. Given the high guidance Apple gave during its Q3 results for future revenue, my inside view is even firmer. This means that I am now disregarding the old analyst recommendations which made me swing toward 'none of the above' before [1].

Reflecting changes in price since last forecast. The numbers for July 30th are 963.6 bln for Apple and 732.1 bln on Amazon. So looking beyond the story-telling, it is highly implausible that Amazon would be the first to get there. So we are left with the question of market direction.
Apple has a market cap of $938B right now, so needs an increase of about 6.6% to pull off a $1T market cap

As of 27/07, APPL is at $954, with earning announcement on 31/7. The stock is relatively volatile, so a 4% upswing over a few days/week is quite possible. Amazon, Alphabet and Microsoft are all below $900 and their earnings announcements for Q2 are passed. They have a strong historical trend, so not impossible to reach 1T before end of year but also not very likely.

As of now, July 26, AAPL - 957.56 Bil Mkt Cap, (4.4% to go) and has earnings release on 31/7 as a catalyst, but AMZN at 904.27 Bil Mkt Cap (10.6%) to go has earnings release at the end of today which could be a catalyst to skyrocket. Alphabet/google and MSFT have already released earnings so I don't see a near-term obvious catalyst. AMZN has higher volatility, with a stronger price uptrend, and investors who don't care as much about current earnings as for Apple.
Based on July 25 data, the official Apple market cap is USD 9.8851921266E11, meaning that only another 1.2 percentage rise is required to reach USD one tln.
There is a reasonable probability none of them will make it because markets go down. Apple is closest than Amazon etc

OK, a bit of witchcraft making this forecast. Be interesting to see how this pans out.

The required return on Apple’s stock is 6.4%. A 6.4% expected capital gain in less than 6 months is improbable. Amazon and Google have a lower market cap, but do not pay a dividend; as such I’ve asssumed a slightly higher expected capital gain for Amazon and Google (a greater percentage of the total return is attributable to capital gains and, as such, the expected increase in the market capitalization is higher).
